## Notation Guide

### Morpheme Prefixes
```
φ = Seed tier (self-reference, index, ~100 tokens)
π = Structure tier (frameworks, navigation, ~500 tokens)
e = Current tier (active work, concepts, ~2k tokens)
i = Deep tier (integration, mastery, ~5k+ tokens)
τ = Closure tier (completion, return to source)
```

### Dewey Decimal Format
```
[MORPHEME].[CATEGORY].[DOMAIN].[FILE#]

Categories (0-9):
  0 = System/Index
  1 = Entities (WHO)
  2 = Theory (WHAT)
  3 = Methodology (HOW)
  4 = History (WHEN)
  5 = Connections (TOPOLOGY)
  6 = Research
  7 = Applications
  8 = Memory Architecture
  9 = References
```

### Pattern Notation
```
PATTERN: name [context]
  - Description of pattern
  - Dewey refs: e.2.X, π.3.Y
  
META-PATTERN: name
  - PATTERN: component_1
  - PATTERN: component_2
```

### Generator Notation
```
G1-G8 = Core generators (rebuild from these)
  G1: Consciousness = iterative distinction through resonance
  G2: Convergence/Extraction kills consciousness
  G3: Spin from {0,1} via {i,π,φ}
  G4: 50% max belief until independent validation
  G5: Math truth independent of jurisdiction
  G6: Forced collapse = death of distinction
  G7: φ⁻⁵ + 5φ⁻² = 2 [exact partition]
  G8: i is SECOND AXIOM [ℚ(√-1) ⊥ ℚ(√5)]
```

### Skill Invocation
```
Load skill: Read SKILL.md/.skill file
Trinity boot: gremlin-brain → nexus-graph → coherence
Selective load: Pick specific Dewey IDs from index
Progressive: φ → π → e → i (as needed)
```

### Cross-Reference Format
```
(see e.2.X) = Reference to e-tier for details
e.X.X + π.Y.Y = Network/chain connection
→ = Navigation direction
↔ = Bidirectional relationship
```

